(1, 12, 13, '2014-02-27', '2013-10-30', 2, 3, 1413323501, 'Sirsi Road, Jaipur - 302021', 'cmat-february-2014-admit-cards-to-be-available-from-5-feb.html', 'CMAT February 2014 Admit Cards to be Available from 5 Feb', '<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px; border: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; border-top-left-radius: 0px !important; border-top-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px !important;">CMAT February 2014 Admit Cards will be available for download on the website of All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) from 05 February 2014 onwards.&nbsp; Aspirants are required to visit the website -- www.aicte-cmat.in and download their admit cards by using login Id and password.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px; border: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; border-top-left-radius: 0px !important; border-top-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px !important;">Common Management Admission Test (CMAT) is a national level entrance exam, conducted by AICTE, for facilitating institutions to determine the eligibility of students for admissions in Management programs approved by AICTE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px; border: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify; border-top-left-radius: 0px !important; border-top-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px !important; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px !important;">CMAT February 2014 is going to be conducted between 20 February and 24 February 2014.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>This is a dummy copy. You&rsquo;re not really s